Notification of Operating Procedure Update

*	The following new or revised ISO Operating Procedures have been
implemented and are posted for reference on the ISO Website.

ISO Operating Procedure posted:  T-121 Sacramento Area Voltage Stability
Version: 3.2
Effective Date: 12/31/2001
Procedure Purpose: This Operating Procedure describes the steps required to
prevent voltage degradation and/or collapse in the Sacramento Area.
Technical studies indicate that low voltage can occur for transmission line
or Generating Unit Outages in the area during summer peak periods. This
Operating Procedure is generally applicable between the months of June
through September. 
Changes / Reasons: Modified EMS References


*	Please find them at
http://www1.caiso.com/thegrid/operations/opsdoc/index.html under the
appropriate Operating Procedure section heading.

